description: Kevin Huizenga, acclaimed author of Curses and Ganges, is back with his fifth installment of Or Else. Stories in this pocket-sized issue include an adaptation of a Giorgio Manganelli tale about a desolate world that is stricken with religious fanaticism and violence, a "special report" on household insects, a profile of a loquacious conversationalist, and an exploration of such important questions as "How are we spending our Tuesday?" Touted as one of the best new talents of his generation, Huizenga is renowned for his bursting creativity and incisive investigations of both the quotidian and the surreal.

An historical novel set in ancient Japan, told with heart and a bellyful of laughs. With his sensitive take on humanity and his completely original artistic vision, Scott Mills' thoughtful tale of early Japan has already proven itself quite popular. ... It has been several thousand years since the end of the last ice age. The waters have warmed and risen, excising great portions of East Asia, while simultaneously creating the cluster of islands we now know as Japan. Across this modest new body of water came many immigrants. Some sought freedom. Some sought fortune. ... When Sun Kim came from Korea to Kyuushuu, the southernmost of the four largest islands of Japan, she was simply looking for a fresh start. ... Complete with panel-by-panel Japanese-language translations, to boot!
name: GN

description: Captain Gonzo and his crew of pirates have it in for Kermie Pan, and with Piggytink's jealousy over Wendy reaching a fever pitch, our green hero may be too distracted by domestic issues to stop him! It's the classic tale of Peter Pan, Muppet Style! Cover by Mouse Guard's David Petersen!

description: After rescuing her father from Palestinian Rebels, Kemette begins her quest to locate various arcane artifacts that will prepare her for the oncoming invasion of the Ophidian Empire. Directed by her father to seek out a famed curator/exporter of things Egyptian, The Sword encounters the Tyrean Sphinx, a mysterious hybrid of human and animal, who seems out for blood and seeking vengeance against the Gods who cursed her with her immortal form. Can Kemette hope to defeat this ancient threat?

A prologue to the three previous books, this issue introduces King Saum, telling the tale of the albino child he abandons in the wilderness. The boy's name is Zal. He is raised in isolation by the mythical Simurgh, and eventually becomes father to Rostam. With his son by his side the great albino sets out on a quest, to help the new king Kai Kavous ascend to the throne of their beloved country, Iran.
name: Search For the King
